author: Bernews
title: Photos: America’s Cup Jam Music Concert
text:
October 18, 2015 | 0 Comments 
Despite the less than welcoming weather, large crowds made their way to Front Street last night [Oct 17] for the America’s Cup Jam presented by Fidelity International, which was headlined by international reggae artists Shaggy and Maxi Priest . 
People, many carrying umbrellas, packed the viewing area to enjoy the concert and gave the entertainers a warm reception as they performed many of their hits from over the years. 
The America’s Cup festivities are set to continue today, with three races scheduled in what has been billed as a “Super Sunday”, with today having more points on offer than any other day in the Louis Vuitton America’s Cup World Series to date. 
- Photos: ACEA/Ricardo Pinto
